% Write `pdd/commands/prompt.py`, implementing the shared `prompt_lint` command used by `pdd checkup lint`.

<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>

% Requirements
- Implement a `prompt_lint` Click command (not a top-level `pdd prompt` group).
- Accept an optional prompt TARGET and optional `--stories <directory>`; require at least one.
- Run `scan_prompt` and `scan_stories` deterministically without network access.
- Support `--json` machine-readable output and `--strict` warning escalation.
- Accept `--review off|explain` (default `off`) using the `review_option` decorator from `pdd.commands.checkup_review_options` to enable the advisory LLM pass. Without `--review explain`, never invoke LLM or cloud-backed work.
- Keep `--llm` as a deprecated alias for `--review explain`: emit one stderr deprecation warning (`click.echo("DeprecationWarning: --llm is deprecated; use --review explain", err=True)`) before forwarding to the advisory path. Keep `--llm` functional.
- Compute the deterministic exit code before any LLM call; the advisory pass MUST NOT alter the exit code.
- When `--review explain` (or `--llm`): inject `"advisory": report_as_dict(report)` as a sibling key per result item in the JSON list; in non-JSON mode print a brief advisory summary to stderr.
- Explicitly document the read-only, advisory nature of the linter in the docstring and help texts.
- Preserve exit codes: 0 for clean, 1 for warnings, 2 for errors or strict warnings.
- Import `SKIPPED_REPORT`, `failed_report`, `final_exit_code`, `report_as_dict` from `pdd.checkup_advisory`.

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/commands/prompt.py`
